OHL May Shortlist Four Bidders for Environment Unit, Cinco Says

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-08-22T06:01:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-22/ohl-may-shortlist-four-bidders-for-environment-unit-cinco-says.html
Spanish construction company
 Obrascon Huarte Lain SA (OHL)  may choose Hong Kong-based  Hutchison
Whampoa Ltd. (13) ,  Brazil ’s Odebrecht SA, South Korea’s  GS
Engineering & Construction Corp. (006360)  and  Posco (005490)  Engineering &
Construction Co., also of South Korea, as preferred bidders for
its environmental business,  Cinco Dias  reported, citing
unidentified people in the industry.  OHL, as the Spanish company is known, aims to sell the
business, valued at 200 million euros ($287 million), by the end
of October, the newspaper said, adding that  Banco Bilbao Vizcaya
Argentaria SA (BBVA)  is advising it on the sale.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net  